SASKATCHEWAN VALLEY LAND COMPANY.

Mr. FOSTER asked :

What ofﬁcial or ofﬁcials of the department authorized, or made the issue of, the patents to the Saskatchewan Land Company, on evi- dence of homestead entries instead of actual settlement, as stated in speech of Clifford Sif- ton, Minister of the Interior, as recorded in ‘ Hansard’ of 1904, page 7035 ?

Hon. FRANK OLIVER (Minister of the Interior). Patents have been issued to the Saskatchewan Valley Land Company for 149,450‘21 acres of land sold to that com- pany with settlement conditions. Such patents were issued on the authority of the Commissioner of Dominion Lands.

The ofﬁcials of the department are unable to ﬁnd in the ‘Hansard’ page mentioned the statement attributed to the Hon. Mr. Si ton.
